# 🎓 3D Hexbin Spring Map

An interactive 3D hexagonal binning visualization built with **MapLibre GL JS** and custom **spring physics animation**. PhD concentration data (synthetic ACS Census-style) is aggregated into hexagonal bins and rendered as extruded 3D columns on a dark basemap.

## ✨ Features

- **3D Hexbin Columns** — height encodes data density with a sunset color ramp
- **Spring Physics Hover** — columns near your cursor bounce up with realistic spring dynamics
- **Wave Intro Animation** — columns pop up west-to-east like dominoes on page load
- **Interactive Map** — pan, zoom, rotate, tilt with MapLibre GL JS
- **CONUS Clipped** — hexagons clipped to US land boundaries
- **Semi-transparent** — basemap visible through columns
- **Zero Dependencies** — single self-contained HTML file

