## 🔧 Customization

### Spring Physics
```javascript
const K = 0.32;     // Stiffness (higher = snappier)
const D = 0.58;     // Damping (lower = bouncier)
const BOOST = 3.5;  // Hover height multiplier
const RAD = 160;    // Effect radius in pixels
```

### Wave Intro
```javascript
const WAVE_MS = 3500; // West-to-east sweep duration (ms)
```

### Your Own Data
Replace the embedded GeoJSON with your own hex-binned data. Each feature needs:
- A numeric value property (used for color + height)
- Hexagonal polygon geometry
- Sequential numeric `id` for feature-state animation

## 📐 Architecture

```
MapLibre GL JS (WebGL basemap + 3D rendering)
  └─ fill-extrusion layer (hex columns)
      └─ feature-state (per-frame height updates)
          └─ Spring physics engine (damped oscillator per hex)
              └─ Mouse proximity detection (screen-space)
```

## 🛠 Tech Stack

- MapLibre GL JS 4.7.1 — open-source WebGL maps
- CartoDB Dark Matter — basemap tiles
- Vanilla JavaScript — no frameworks, no build step
- TypedArrays — Float64Array for 60fps performance

